description: Long position of a 3-month Zero Coupon Bond starting at 01/02/2015 with Notional of 1000 and Discount at Purchase of 100.
Same as case 101 but short position.
Same as case 101 but with single coupon payment at fixed Nominal Rate of 1% instead of Discount at Purchase.
Long position of a 5-year Coupon Bearing Bond starting at 01/02/2015 with Notional of 1000. Coupon payments are made annually at fixed Nominal Rate of 2% using Day Count Convention 30/360.
Same as case 104 but short position.
Same as case 104 but with semi-annually Coupon payments.
Same as case 104 but using A/A-ISDA Day Count Convention.
Same as case 104 but applying a Weekday-Calendar and Shift-Calculate-Forward BusinessDayConvention.
Same as case 104 but uneven last coupon period is handled differently (short stub).
Same as case 104 but with Coupon being fixed and paid at beginning of Interest period (CyclePointOfInterestPayment=0) rather than end.
Same as case 104 but with an Interest Capitalization period up to 01/02/2017.

Long position of a 10-year Coupon Bearing Bond starting at 01/02/2015 with Notional of 1000. Coupon payments are made annually at floating rates calculated as forward rates based on todays reference Yield Curve + a Spread of 2%.
Same as case 112 but with variable rates being fixed bi-annually.
Same as case 113 but with variable rates being fixed within Coupon periods.
Long position of a 10-year Coupon Bearing Bond starting at 01/02/2015 with Notional of 1000. Coupon payments are made annually at fixed (base) Nominal Rate of 5% and linked to a Reference Index.
Same as case 115 but also Notional amount is linked to the Reference Index.

Long position of a 7-year Coupon Bearing Bond starting at 01/02/2021 with Notional of 1000. Coupon payments are made annually at floating rates calculated as forward rates based on todays reference Yield Curve + a Spread of 2%.
Same as case 112 but with variable rates being fixed bi-annually.

Long position of a 7-year Coupon Bearing Bond starting at 01/02/2022 with Notional of 1000. Coupon payments are made annually at floating rates calculated as forward rates based on todays reference Yield Curve + a Spread of 2%.
